Ncmpcpp setup is pretty straightforward, but here's some links for nice presets.

https://computingforgeeks.com/how-to-configure-mpd-and-ncmpcpp-on-linux/
https://twily.info/.ncmpcpp/config <- full breakdown for what all the parts do.
http://dotshare.it/dots/1533/

most important part

## Available values:
##
## - 0 - default window color (discards all other colors)
## - 1 - black
## - 2 - red
## - 3 - green
## - 4 - yellow
## - 5 - blue
## - 6 - magenta
## - 7 - cyan
## - 8 - white
## - 9 - end of current color
##
## Note: colors can be nested.
##
